article.description: Derrick Woods recorded 17 points and 10 rebounds to lead St. Peter's to an 86-70 win over Fairleigh Dickinson on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Woods leads St. Peter's over Fairleigh Dickinson 86-70
article.linkText: Woods leads St. Peter's over Fairleigh Dickinson 86-70
article.story: JERSEY CITY, N.J. -- Derrick Woods recorded 17 points and 10 rebounds to lead St. Peter's to an 86-70 win over Fairleigh Dickinson on Wednesday night. Fousseyni Drame had 15 points and nine rebounds for St. Peter's (2-4). Doug Edert added 14 points. Quinn Taylor had 13 points for the home team. Jahlil Jenkins had 19 points and five steals for the Knights (2-7). Kaleb Bishop added 16 points. Xzavier Malone-Key had 13 points. St. Peter's takes on UConn on the road next Wednesday. Fairleigh Dickinson faces Princeton at home on Saturday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
